WEBVTT

00:05.223 --> 00:05.931
I'm Frances Everdell.

00:05.931 --> 00:07.307
It's Skip,
nice to meet you.

00:07.307 --> 00:09.098
You too. And-- And-- Bye.

00:09.764 --> 00:11.348
We should officially
do business.

00:11.348 --> 00:13.598
I buy the houses
and you design and renovate.

00:13.598 --> 00:15.265
And we turn a tidy profit.

00:15.265 --> 00:16.806
Hate to say,
but I do like it.

00:17.473 --> 00:19.806
You loaned me money,
which I appreciate,

00:19.806 --> 00:21.598
but we're not actually partners.

00:22.432 --> 00:23.973
That prick from the auction,
he's here.

00:23.973 --> 00:25.223
Can I take you out
for dinner some time?

00:25.223 --> 00:27.473
I would feel impolite accepting
when I'm here

00:27.473 --> 00:28.307
with someone else.

00:28.598 --> 00:30.307
It's too soon
for me to be getting involved.

00:30.307 --> 00:31.723
Yeah, I think
my exact words were,

00:31.723 --> 00:33.848
you were a walking disaster.
And my instincts were right.

00:34.806 --> 00:36.514
Skip Zakarian wants to rep me.

00:36.514 --> 00:38.473
This means that
we won't be working together.

00:38.473 --> 00:40.598
You weren't even finishing
your paintings when I met you.

00:40.598 --> 00:42.681
Thanks for everything,
I'm done here.

00:59.015 --> 01:00.848
- Hi!
- Hey.

01:02.806 --> 01:04.182
Did you study
for your math final?

01:04.182 --> 01:06.473
- Yes, I did.
- Oh, you're so good.

01:06.473 --> 01:08.556
Yeah, he got out
the old abacus

01:08.556 --> 01:10.140
and kicked some butt.

01:10.140 --> 01:12.681
Mom, wait till you hear
about summer.

01:14.348 --> 01:16.015
What about--
what about summer?

01:17.098 --> 01:19.681
- Um...
- Thank you.

01:19.681 --> 01:24.639
You know, we, uh...
maybe hoping to...

01:24.639 --> 01:25.890
take the kids to Italy.

01:25.890 --> 01:28.848
- Yeah.

01:28.848 --> 01:31.140
With your permission,
of course.

01:31.140 --> 01:33.056
She's got
an old college roommate

01:33.056 --> 01:36.848
that made
a shitload of money
selling hair extensions

01:36.848 --> 01:39.223
and bought a villa--
in Italy.

01:39.223 --> 01:43.556
And even
has a
big fucking moat.

01:43.556 --> 01:47.307
And she's offered it
to us for free,

01:47.307 --> 01:51.056
um, you know, for June.

01:51.056 --> 01:51.973
And July.

01:51.973 --> 01:53.973
For June and

01:53.973 --> 01:56.182
- Yeah.
- Well, I don't want
to be without the kids

01:56.182 --> 01:58.223
for all of June and July.

01:58.223 --> 02:00.307
I mean,
summer's the only time
I have with them

02:00.307 --> 02:02.723
when they're not just...

02:02.723 --> 02:05.390
cranky all the time
from too little sleep.

02:05.390 --> 02:08.098
- You know.
- Yeah, but they've never
been to Europe.

02:08.098 --> 02:10.307
Well, I'm well aware
of that.

02:10.307 --> 02:12.390
As you know,
it has been my dream

02:12.390 --> 02:15.307
to take them,
and as you also well know,

02:15.307 --> 02:18.514
we haven't been able
to afford that.

02:21.432 --> 02:26.098
I'm sorry, but it's a no.

02:26.098 --> 02:28.681
And you should've told me
before you spoke to them

02:28.681 --> 02:32.890
because now--
shit, now I'm in this,
like, lousy position.

02:32.890 --> 02:34.432
Once again,
I'm the dream killer.

02:34.432 --> 02:36.307
Well, if the scarpe  fits.

02:36.307 --> 02:39.056
- That's "shoe" in Italian.
- Yes, it's-- yes, I know.

02:39.056 --> 02:42.806
- We were studying
last night, but, yeah.
Already?

02:42.806 --> 02:45.432
No worries.
You know, we'll-- okay.

02:45.432 --> 02:49.931
- Ciao,  which is
"good-bye" and "hello."
- Yeah, ciao,  as in Italian.

02:49.931 --> 02:51.514
- I know.
- Yeah.

02:51.514 --> 02:52.473
So,  ciao.

03:11.556 --> 03:14.307
What the fuck?

03:14.307 --> 03:16.681
Ugh, this is bullshit!

03:16.681 --> 03:18.015
I wish it were.

03:18.015 --> 03:19.723
Where's the part
about you finding her

03:19.723 --> 03:21.182
and us
launching her career, huh?

03:21.182 --> 03:22.890
- Oh, nowhere.

03:22.890 --> 03:25.473
Nowhere. I am
officially scrubbed

03:25.473 --> 03:27.140
from her entire history.

03:27.140 --> 03:30.307
I never
trusted that Sylvia,
but Skip?

03:30.307 --> 03:32.223
I went to St. Barts
with Skip.

03:32.223 --> 03:33.598
He was, like, my pal.

03:33.598 --> 03:35.098
Well, your pal is taking

03:35.098 --> 03:37.265
every ounce of credit
for Sylvia.

03:37.265 --> 03:38.931
Yeah, and all
our future profits.

03:38.931 --> 03:40.390
I'm like training wheels.

03:40.390 --> 03:43.056
I get them started,
I give them a little shove,

03:43.056 --> 03:44.265
and then they ride off

03:44.265 --> 03:45.639
on their
brand-new two-wheelers

03:45.639 --> 03:47.265
into the sunset without me.

03:47.265 --> 03:49.764
Oh, and get this--
Robert and Jackie

03:49.764 --> 03:51.931
want to take the kids
to Europe this summer.

03:51.931 --> 03:54.848
- That's great.
- No, it's not great,
Diane, it's not.

03:54.848 --> 03:58.348
I don't want to spend
the whole summer alone
without them.

03:58.348 --> 03:59.514
Oh, my God, please.

03:59.514 --> 04:00.514
If I had kids, all I'd want

04:00.514 --> 04:02.015
was a long break from them.

04:02.015 --> 04:04.348
Well, then
it's probably good

04:04.348 --> 04:06.265
you never had them.

04:06.265 --> 04:09.973
Yeah. You know
what, Frances?

04:09.973 --> 04:13.681
Maybe Sylvia and Robert
were like training wheels
for you, you know?

04:13.681 --> 04:14.848
It's like when
I was working

04:14.848 --> 04:16.723
at the glove counter
at Saks

04:16.723 --> 04:19.681
and living
in that tiny studio
in the East 50s.

04:19.681 --> 04:20.890
I just loved my life.

04:20.890 --> 04:22.223
And then I met Nick

04:22.223 --> 04:24.432
and my life got
even bigger and better!

04:24.432 --> 04:26.390
So you just
don't know, Frances.

04:26.390 --> 04:28.348
You don't know
what the future holds.

04:28.348 --> 04:32.598
Apparently, it holds
a lot of blank walls.

04:32.598 --> 04:35.223
I'm just gonna be glad
to get these Sylvias
out of here

04:35.223 --> 04:36.348
and to their new owners.

04:37.764 --> 04:39.098
Who's that?

04:39.098 --> 04:40.931
Oh, some kid
up the road did it.

04:40.931 --> 04:42.681
I didn't have the heart
to tell him

04:42.681 --> 04:44.098
that it looked like
one of those elephants

04:44.098 --> 04:45.098
holding a paintbrush
made it.

04:46.265 --> 04:48.973
- Diane.

04:48.973 --> 04:52.390
You know what?
I like it.

04:52.390 --> 04:57.265
It's bright, it's happy,
I don't love it.

04:57.265 --> 04:59.639
Can't hurt me.
I'm borrowing it.

04:59.639 --> 05:01.723
Please, thank God.

05:06.598 --> 05:08.473
Motherfucker!

05:14.931 --> 05:17.514
- Man: Certainly.

05:17.514 --> 05:20.307
Frances. It's good
to see you.

05:20.307 --> 05:23.265
Really? Is it
good to see me?

05:23.265 --> 05:26.265
'Cause I have some things
to say to you, asshole.

05:26.265 --> 05:28.432
Well, okay, you're--
you're coming in hot.

05:28.432 --> 05:33.931
Maybe poaching Sylvia
was some sort of pathetic
dick swing payback

05:33.931 --> 05:35.723
for my declining
your dinner invitation.

05:35.723 --> 05:37.848
- It wasn't.
- Okay, well, regardless,

05:37.848 --> 05:40.973
it was a full-on
shady thing to do.

05:40.973 --> 05:42.432
So, I'm gonna--
gonna give you

05:42.432 --> 05:44.514
a little background--
a little history, okay?

05:44.514 --> 05:49.348
When I met Sylvia,
she was in a total
artistic coma.

05:49.348 --> 05:51.890
I worked with her
and I sure as hell
didn't do it

05:51.890 --> 05:57.140
so that you could show up
in your fancy car service
one night and steal her.

05:57.140 --> 05:58.723
I mean,
is that what you do?

05:58.723 --> 06:01.473
Pretty much, yes.

06:01.473 --> 06:04.182
- Wow, how-- how
do you sleep at night?
- Look, I don't have the eye

06:04.182 --> 06:06.473
or, frankly, the energy
to do what you do.

06:06.473 --> 06:08.056
I wish I did.

06:08.056 --> 06:09.848
But once an artist
is on my radar,

06:09.848 --> 06:11.307
I can sell
the shit out of them.

06:11.307 --> 06:12.639
I know what people want,

06:12.639 --> 06:14.265
I know how much money
these people have,

06:14.265 --> 06:15.806
and I know where
they've parked their yachts.

06:15.806 --> 06:17.556
So, the way I see it,
you can go on

06:17.556 --> 06:19.639
having people like me
steal your artists

06:19.639 --> 06:23.307
or we could discuss
working together.

06:23.307 --> 06:24.556
Are you serious?

06:24.556 --> 06:26.473
You fuck me over
and then you expect me

06:26.473 --> 06:28.681
to go into business
with you?

06:28.681 --> 06:31.514
- Oh, that's rich.
- Hey, you can stay
in your sleepy little hamlet

06:31.514 --> 06:34.890
and watch people leave you
or you can move forward.

06:34.890 --> 06:35.848
That's my two cents.

06:36.931 --> 06:38.348
Unbelievable.

06:38.348 --> 06:42.764
Oh, and, uh, here.

06:42.764 --> 06:46.598
You can keep your two cents
and your pricey trinket.

06:46.598 --> 06:47.848
I'm not for sale.

06:50.265 --> 06:51.556
Call me
if you want to talk.

06:51.556 --> 06:53.473
Jesus.

06:53.473 --> 06:56.764
Woman:
So, all profits
on future investments

06:56.764 --> 06:58.348
are split 50-50.

06:58.348 --> 07:01.348
- Yep.
- All righty, if you both sign

07:01.348 --> 07:06.348
