your real estate partnership
is finalized.

07:06.348 --> 07:09.307
Check that out.
What a signature.

07:09.307 --> 07:10.556
You should've seen it
in high school.

07:10.556 --> 07:12.681
It actually included
a smiley face.

07:12.681 --> 07:14.223
- Aw.

07:14.223 --> 07:16.639
- Well, congratulations...
- That's sweet.

07:16.639 --> 07:18.265
...you are now
a corporation.

07:18.265 --> 07:20.556
And if I could just say,

07:20.556 --> 07:22.890
- you two are adorable.
- Oh.

07:22.890 --> 07:25.307
- You're pretty cute
yourself, Michelle.
- Michelle: Well, thank you.

07:25.307 --> 07:27.098
And you work well together.

07:27.098 --> 07:28.598
These agreements
are difficult,

07:28.598 --> 07:29.890
believe you me.

07:29.890 --> 07:31.390
Basically, it's like
doing a prenup,

07:31.390 --> 07:34.265
but you guys just
breezed on through.

07:35.890 --> 07:39.348
- Oh, thank you.

07:51.556 --> 07:53.556
Shit.

07:55.098 --> 07:56.598
Come on.

08:03.764 --> 08:04.931
Oh, my--

08:09.015 --> 08:11.639
Oh! Oh, my God.

08:11.639 --> 08:13.723
Holy shit.

08:21.806 --> 08:23.514
Thanks for coming.

08:23.514 --> 08:24.890
I didn't know
who else to call.

08:24.890 --> 08:26.140
Plumbers.

08:26.140 --> 08:28.056
- This is their profession.

08:28.056 --> 08:29.764
Just throwing it out there.

08:29.764 --> 08:31.848
Of course.
Yeah, no, it's better
to call a plumber,

08:31.848 --> 08:34.390
but I panicked,
'cause that was, like,
shooting at me sideways.

08:34.390 --> 08:37.639
Oh, and by the way,
we have no water pressure
in the upstairs shower

08:37.639 --> 08:39.639
and that was
like a fire hose.

08:39.639 --> 08:41.307
If that's a veiled attempt
to get me to fix

08:41.307 --> 08:43.432
the showerhead,
no way, José.

08:43.432 --> 08:45.973
Oh, no, no,
just this one job, sir.

08:47.556 --> 08:49.931
'Cause you know this house
better than anyone.

08:49.931 --> 08:52.931
This house and I
have been through
many  emotional highs

08:52.931 --> 08:55.639
and lows together.

08:55.639 --> 08:58.598
Hey, so, what,
your-- your fella

08:58.598 --> 08:59.973
not available
to come help?

08:59.973 --> 09:02.140
He's not my fella.

09:02.140 --> 09:05.681
- And we're done.
Copy that.

09:05.681 --> 09:07.056
Seemed like
a nice guy, though.

09:07.056 --> 09:10.140
Except for, you know,
those weird sweater-vests.

09:10.140 --> 09:12.307
He did not
wear sweater-vests.

09:12.307 --> 09:14.723
In his soul,
he was wearing
a sweater-vest.

09:14.723 --> 09:18.432
- No.
- Oh, reminds me.

09:18.432 --> 09:20.973
I have something for you.

09:23.015 --> 09:23.890
Here you go.

09:28.473 --> 09:30.140
$75,000?

09:30.140 --> 09:32.723
Finally started
to make some money
on these flip houses.

09:32.723 --> 09:35.348
And I just wanted
to pay you back.

09:35.348 --> 09:37.681
'Cause, you know,
you supported me--

09:37.681 --> 09:41.307
well, the family--
for so long.

09:42.639 --> 09:43.848
Really long time.

09:43.848 --> 09:45.598
You trying to buy me
off so you can take

09:45.598 --> 09:46.723
the kids this summer?

09:46.723 --> 09:49.307
Jesus. Just say thanks

09:49.307 --> 09:51.556
and invest in a new pipe.

09:52.681 --> 09:54.056
Thank you.

09:55.390 --> 09:57.806
Really... thank you.

09:58.848 --> 10:01.764
And congratulations on...

10:01.764 --> 10:04.307
you know, the houses,
on everything.

10:04.307 --> 10:06.432
Thanks. It feels good.

10:09.265 --> 10:11.098
It's really weird,
I never imagined

10:11.098 --> 10:14.098
when we first
bought this place...

10:14.098 --> 10:17.140
you know,
that we wouldn't be...

10:17.140 --> 10:18.473
- Yeah.
- Huh, it's weird.

10:18.473 --> 10:21.348
I thought
I would drop dead
in this house.

10:21.348 --> 10:23.890
- Do you ever wonder,

10:23.890 --> 10:27.348
like... what if we met
each other now?

10:28.556 --> 10:31.973
You mean if New Frances
met New Robert?

10:31.973 --> 10:33.723
Yeah. Yeah.

10:33.723 --> 10:35.931
- I think we'd have
a lot of laughs.
- Yeah.

10:35.931 --> 10:38.806
Mostly at the expense
of-- of Old Frances.

10:38.806 --> 10:43.681
- Hi, I'm Frances.

10:43.681 --> 10:45.973
- Swifty.

10:45.973 --> 10:49.473
New Robert
gets to call himself
whatever he wants.

10:58.973 --> 11:00.598
- Oh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- Oh.

11:00.598 --> 11:03.098
- I'm so sorry. Oh.
- I can't do it again.

11:03.098 --> 11:05.265
- No, of course not. It--
- I'm with Jackie.

11:05.265 --> 11:08.265
No, I-- I know that.
I know that.

11:08.265 --> 11:09.931
I'm sorry.

11:19.432 --> 11:21.265
Diane:
I don't know, Frances,
that whole Skip idea

11:21.265 --> 11:22.598
sounds kind of tempting.

11:22.598 --> 11:23.806
- We could team up with him

11:23.806 --> 11:25.015
and make a killing,
come on!

11:25.015 --> 11:27.182
I don't want
to make a killing!

11:27.182 --> 11:30.140
I want to enjoy what I do.

11:30.140 --> 11:32.973
You know,
I used to enjoy art.

11:32.973 --> 11:36.307
This whole Sylvia business
has just--

11:36.307 --> 11:38.848
has left a very bad taste
in my mouth.

11:38.848 --> 11:41.056
All right,
forget about business
and we can have some fun.

11:41.056 --> 11:43.432
Hey, you're coming
to our Memorial Day barbecue
this Sunday, right?

11:43.432 --> 11:45.307
- Yeah, I'll be there.
- Yay!

11:45.307 --> 11:47.307
Oh, and Nick invited
Robert and Jackie.

11:47.307 --> 11:50.639
- Yeah, absolutely.

11:50.639 --> 11:52.556
No, we're good, so, yeah,
there's no worries there--

11:52.556 --> 11:57.806
Whoa wait.
This reminds me. Um... here.

11:58.848 --> 11:59.806
I want you to have this.

12:02.140 --> 12:03.723
A check made out to you?

12:03.723 --> 12:05.390
Well, no, I mean,
Robert made it out to me,

12:05.390 --> 12:07.307
and I endorsed it to you.

12:07.307 --> 12:10.681
See? It's to pay you back.

12:10.681 --> 12:12.806
- For the gallery loan.
- Oh!

12:12.806 --> 12:15.015
I mean, I can't think
of no better recipient
than you.

12:15.015 --> 12:16.973
You've done
so much for me, Diane.

12:16.973 --> 12:20.015
- So thank you.
- You don't have
to do this, Frances.

12:20.015 --> 12:23.890
No, I-- I want to do it.
I'm proud to do it.

12:25.056 --> 12:28.307
Oh, I see.
So this is how it ends.

12:28.307 --> 12:29.598
Wait, what?

12:29.598 --> 12:31.848
Now that
the dreadful Pelts
is gone,

12:31.848 --> 12:33.848
you just don't have
any more use for me.

12:33.848 --> 12:35.681
No, Diane,
please don't make this

12:35.681 --> 12:37.056
something that it isn't,
all right?

12:37.056 --> 12:39.140
I-- I have been
telling you for so long

12:39.140 --> 12:40.348
that I'm gonna pay
you back

12:40.348 --> 12:41.432
and I feel like
you just chose

12:41.432 --> 12:42.890
to not hear me.

12:42.890 --> 12:46.681
I'm giving you money.
It's a good thing.

12:46.681 --> 12:48.390
Yeah, for you, I guess.

12:48.390 --> 12:51.848
- Oh, come on. Diane!
- No.

12:51.848 --> 12:55.556
You wanted to do
the gallery alone,
now I want to be alone.

12:55.556 --> 12:57.098
- Yeah.

12:57.098 --> 12:58.182
Don't try and stop me.

12:59.432 --> 13:02.514
- Okay.
- You can Uber home!

13:02.514 --> 13:06.182
I-- there's no service.

13:07.890 --> 13:10.265
Oh, come on. Diane!

13:12.056 --> 13:13.265
Good.

13:13.265 --> 13:14.723
You know what would be fun
to do in Italy?

13:14.723 --> 13:16.098
Buy leather.

13:16.098 --> 13:18.890
Yes!

13:18.890 --> 13:20.390
Get married.

13:20.390 --> 13:21.265
Wait, what?

13:22.806 --> 13:25.598
You know,
that butterscotch candy
lawyer was right.

13:25.598 --> 13:28.265
I mean,
we did the hard work.

13:28.265 --> 13:30.764
And-- and we work together.

13:30.764 --> 13:32.223
Really well.

13:32.223 --> 13:35.223
I know it's really fast...

13:35.223 --> 13:38.514
but my marriage lasted
a long time and look where
that ended up.

13:38.514 --> 13:39.473
I mean,
life's short, Jackie.

13:40.931 --> 13:43.931
I don't remember
what that quote was

13:43.931 --> 13:46.390
from that inspirational,
cheesy poster,

13:46.390 --> 13:50.432
but... I want
my future to start.

13:53.598 --> 13:54.723
Today.

13:57.931 --> 14:00.432
You're asking me
to marry you.

14:02.432 --> 14:03.764
Will you marry me?

14:05.848 --> 14:08.265
- Fuck yeah!
- Fuck yeah.

14:09.514 --> 14:10.639
Oh!

14:12.140 --> 14:14.723
- Say it again!
- Man: Fuck Frances.

14:14.723 --> 14:17.182
- Say it again!
- Fuck Frances!

14:17.182 --> 14:19.432
I was the best
goddamn partner
she ever had.

14:19.432 --> 14:21.639
I knew her peccadilloes,
her needs,

14:21.639 --> 14:23.681
and let me
tell you something, Dwayne,

14:23.681 --> 14:27.639
this lady is not
a walk in the park.

14:27.639 --> 14:29.681
- Fuck her!
- Thank you, Dwayne.

14:29.681 --> 14:31.015
And I wanna tell
you something--

14:31.015 --> 14:31.973
I really like you.

14:31.973 --> 14:33.890
You're a good person.

14:33.890 --> 14:36.265
May I buy you a new cap?

14:37.348 --> 14:38.723
- Okay.
- Okay.

14:42.140 --> 14:44.140
But first,
